 Appearances (Points). Wayne Swart is a South African rugby union player, currently playing with the Eastern Province Kings.[1] Born in Johannesburg, he started his rugby career playing for local provincial team the Golden Lions in youth competitions. In 2008, he was included in the Vodacom Cup squad. He represented the team several times in this competition, as well as the Currie Cup competition, but failed to make the breakthrough into the Super Rugby squad. He joined Eastern Province Kings for the 2012 Vodacom Cup season.[2]
